ry\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>ḥṭʾlm: a hapax in phoenician onomastics. mms: punic personal name, unexplained. bʿlytn: phoenician personal name “Baal has given”, Latin transcription attested in various inscriptions, e.g.: BALITHONIS (CIL V 4920), BALIATON (CIL VIII 16011, 27491), BALIATHO (CIL VIII 68, AE 1992 1781).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> De Simone 2023 55 fig.1 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002543\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10002543\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-5  58-105  Interlineation line 1 to 2    \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[191,194,197,200,203,205,208,211,214],{"id":192,"html":193},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy De Simone, 2014-07\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive-transliteration\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"xpu-Latn\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>mnṣpt \u003Cspan class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"ḥṭʾlm\n                    mms\n                    bn bʿ\n                    lytn\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"ḥṭʾlm\">ḥṭʾlm\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"mms\">mms\u003C/span>  \u003Cspan class=\"tei text-direction r-to-l\"> &nbsp;&nbsp;←\u003